---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Slides">
  <p>The <code>slides</code> array defines your presentation content. Each item creates one slide.</p>

  <h2>Basic Slide</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">slides:
  - background: $bg
    elements:
      - type: text
        x: 1
        y: 2
        w: 8
        h: 1
        text: "Hello, World!"
        size: 36
        bold: true</code></pre>

  <h2>Slide with Master</h2>
  <p>Reference a defined master and pass data for its placeholders:</p>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">slides:
  - master: section_header
    data:
      title: "Financial Highlights"
      description: "Revenue and growth metrics"</code></pre>

  <h2>Slide Properties</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Key</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>master</code></td><td>string</td><td>Name of a master template to use</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>data</code></td><td>object</td><td>Key-value pairs for master placeholders</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>background</code></td><td>string</td><td>Slide background color</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>elements</code></td><td>array</td><td>List of elements on this slide</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Combining Masters and Elements</h2>
  <p>A slide can inherit a master's layout and add additional elements:</p>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">slides:
  - master: content_slide
    data:
      title: "Revenue Trend"
    elements:
      - type: chart
        chart: bar
        x: 0.5
        y: 1.5
        w: 9
        h: 3.5
        series:
          - name: "Revenue"
            labels: ["Q1", "Q2", "Q3"]
            values: [2800, 3200, 3700]</code></pre>
  <p>The master renders its background and title, then the chart is layered on top.</p>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  th, td {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    text-align: left;
  }
  th {
    background: #f1f5f9;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
